HEADWORD: Xylopyrography
<hw>Xy`lo*py*rog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Xylo-</ets> + Gr. <?/, <?/, fire + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The art or practice of burning pictures on wood with a hot iron; --
called also <altname>wood burning</altname> and <altname>poker
painting</altname>. See <cref>Poker picture</cref>, under
<er>Poker</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

